Task 8: Theme

Theming in CSS involves creating different styles for different themes, such as light and dark mode.

Example of a simple theme switcher using Sass:

$light-theme-color: #fff;
$dark-theme-color: #222;

$is-dark-theme: false;

body {
  background-color: if($is-dark-theme, $dark-theme-color, $light-theme-color);
  color: if($is-dark-theme, $light-theme-color, $dark-theme-color);
}

// ... other theme-specific styles

To switch themes, you can toggle the $is-dark-theme variable using JavaScript or other techniques.